HB 810 Original 2026 Regular Session Bourriaque
Abstract: Provides for additional authorized uses of the investment of public funds to
capitalize a state infrastructure bank.
Present constitution confines the investment of public funds to capitalize a state
infrastructure bank solely to transportation projects.
Proposed constitutional amendment retains present constitution and expands the use of the
investment to water, energy, resilience, and hazard mitigation projects.
Provides for submission of the proposed amendment to the voters at the statewide election
to be held Nov. 3, 2026.
(Amends Const. Art. VII, §14(B))
